1: -module(vehicle_SUITE).
    2: -include("public_transport.hrl").
    3: -include("time.hrl").
    4: -include_lib("common_test/include/ct.hrl").
    5: -include_lib("eunit/include/eunit.hrl"). %% For assertion macros
    6: 
    7: -export([ checkin_ok_case/1
    8:         , boarding_passenger_capacity_reached_case/1
    9:         , boarding_passenger_below_capacity_case/1
   10:         , next_stop_reached_case/1
   11:         , next_stop_not_reached_case/1
   12:         , target_stop_reached_case/1
   13:         , increment_boarding_passenger_case/1
   14:         , new_time_not_driving_case/1]).
   15: 
   16: -export([ all/0
   17:         , init_per_testcase/2
   18:         , end_per_testcase/2]).
   19: 
   20: all() ->
   21:   [ checkin_ok_case
   22:   , boarding_passenger_capacity_reached_case
   23:   , boarding_passenger_below_capacity_case
   24:   , next_stop_reached_case
   25:   , next_stop_not_reached_case
   26:   , target_stop_reached_case
   27:   , increment_boarding_passenger_case
   28:   , new_time_not_driving_case
   29:   ].
   30: 
   31: init_per_testcase(Config) ->
   32:   vehicle_supervisor:start_link(),
   33:   StartStop = gen_server_mock:start(stop, startstop, strict),
   34:   TargetStop = gen_server_mock:start(stop, targetstop, strict),
   35:   Time = gen_server_mock:start_global(time, time, strict),
   36:   PT = gen_server_mock:start_global(public_transport, public_transport, strict),
   37:   S1 = gen_server_mock:start(stop, s1, strict),
   38:   P1 = gen_server_mock:start(citizen, p1, strict),
   39:   P2 = gen_server_mock:start(citizen, p2, strict),
   40:   P3 = gen_server_mock:start(citizen, p3, strict),
   41:   P4 = gen_server_mock:start(citizen, p4, strict),
   42: 
   43:   gen_server_mock:expect_ets_lookup(public_transport, ?LINE_ID(bus, 1), [StartStop, 5, TargetStop]),
   44: 
   45:   Config ++ [ {startstop, StartStop}
   46:             , {targetstop, TargetStop}
   47:             , {time, Time}
   48:             , {pt, PT}
   49:             , {s1, S1}
   50:             , {p1, P1}
   51:             , {p2, P2}
   52:             , {p3, P3}
   53:             , {p4, P4}
   54:             ].
   55: 
   56: init_per_testcase(TestCase, Config) ->
   57:   UpdatedConfig = init_per_testcase(Config),
   58:   StartStop = ?config(startstop, UpdatedConfig),
   59:   TargetStop = ?config(targetstop, UpdatedConfig),
   60:   Time = ?config(time, UpdatedConfig),
   61:   PT = ?config(pt, UpdatedConfig),
   62:   HasThreeCapacity = lists:member(TestCase, [ checkin_ok_case
   63:                                             , boarding_passenger_capacity_reached_case
   64:                                             , boarding_passenger_below_capacity_case
   65:                                             , new_time_not_driving_case
   66:                                             ]),
   67:   HasFourCapacity = lists:member(TestCase, [ next_stop_reached_case
   68:                                            , next_stop_not_reached_case
   69:                                            , target_stop_reached_case
   70:                                            , increment_boarding_passenger_case
   71:                                            ]),
   72:   Vehicle = vehicle_supervisor:start_vehicle(if
   73:                                                HasThreeCapacity -> 3;
   74:                                                HasFourCapacity -> 4
   75:                                              end, 1, TargetStop, bus),
   76:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(Time, {?SUBSCRIBE, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
   77:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(StartStop, {?VEHICLE_CHECK_IN, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
   78: 
   79:   [{vehicle, Vehicle}|UpdatedConfig].
   80: 
   81: 
   82: 
   83: end_per_testcase(_TestCase, Config) ->
   84:   StartStop = ?config(startstop, Config),
   85:   TargetStop = ?config(targetstop, Config),
   86:   Time = ?config(time, Config),
   87:   PT = ?config(pt, Config),
   88:   S1 = ?config(s1, Config),
   89:   P1 = ?config(p1, Config),
   90:   P2 = ?config(p2, Config),
   91:   P3 = ?config(p3, Config),
   92:   P4 = ?config(p4, Config),
   93:   Vehicle = ?config(vehicle, Config),
   94:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(StartStop)),
   95:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(TargetStop)),
   96:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(Time)),
   97:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(PT)),
   98:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(S1)),
   99:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(P1)),
  100:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(P2)),
  101:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(P3)),
  102:   ?assert(gen_server_mock:validate(P4)),
  103:   gen_server_mock:stop(StartStop),
  104:   gen_server_mock:stop(TargetStop),
  105:   gen_server_mock:stop(Time),
  106:   gen_server_mock:stop(PT),
  107:   gen_server_mock:stop(S1),
  108:   gen_server_mock:stop(P1),
  109:   gen_server_mock:stop(P2),
  110:   gen_server_mock:stop(P3),
  111:   gen_server_mock:stop(P4),
  112:   vehicle_supervisor:stop_vehicle(Vehicle),
  113:   Config.
  114: 
  115: 
  116: checkin_ok_case(Config) ->
  117:   StartStop = ?config(startstop, Config),
  118:   TargetStop = ?config(targetstop, Config),
  119:   Time = ?config(time, Config),
  120:   PT = ?config(pt, Config),
  121:   S1 = ?config(s1, Config),
  122:   P1 = ?config(p1, Config),
  123:   P2 = ?config(p2, Config),
  124:   P3 = ?config(p3, Config),
  125:   P4 = ?config(p4, Config),
  126:   Vehicle = ?config(vehicle, Config),
  127: 
  128:   gen_server_mock:expect_ets_lookup(public_transport, ?LINE_ID(bus, 1), [StartStop, 5, S1, 7, TargetStop]),
  129:   gen_server_mock:expect_ets_lookup(time, time, 1234),
  130:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(StartStop, {?VEHICLE_CHECK_OUT, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
  131:   vehicle:?CHECKIN_OK(Vehicle, StartStop, 0, true).
  132: 
  133: boarding_passenger_capacity_reached_case(Config) ->
  134:   StartStop = ?config(startstop, Config),
  135:   TargetStop = ?config(targetstop, Config),
  136:   Time = ?config(time, Config),
  137:   PT = ?config(pt, Config),
  138:   S1 = ?config(s1, Config),
  139:   P1 = ?config(p1, Config),
  140:   P2 = ?config(p2, Config),
  141:   P3 = ?config(p3, Config),
  142:   P4 = ?config(p4, Config),
  143:   Vehicle = ?config(vehicle, Config),
  144: 
  145:   vehicle:?CHECKIN_OK(Vehicle, StartStop, 4, true),
  146:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P1), ok),
  147:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P2), ok),
  148: 
  149:   gen_server_mock:expect_ets_lookup(public_transport, ?LINE_ID(bus, 1), [StartStop, 5, S1, 7, TargetStop]),
  150:   gen_server_mock:expect_ets_lookup(time, time, 1234),
  151:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(StartStop, {?VEHICLE_CHECK_OUT, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
  152:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P3), ok),
  153:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P4), nok).
  154: 
  155: boarding_passenger_below_capacity_case(Config) ->
  156:   StartStop = ?config(startstop, Config),
  157:   TargetStop = ?config(targetstop, Config),
  158:   Time = ?config(time, Config),
  159:   PT = ?config(pt, Config),
  160:   S1 = ?config(s1, Config),
  161:   P1 = ?config(p1, Config),
  162:   P2 = ?config(p2, Config),
  163:   P3 = ?config(p3, Config),
  164:   P4 = ?config(p4, Config),
  165:   Vehicle = ?config(vehicle, Config),
  166: 
  167:   vehicle:?CHECKIN_OK(Vehicle, StartStop, 3, true),
  168:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P1), ok),
  169:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P2), ok),
  170: 
  171:   gen_server_mock:expect_ets_lookup(public_transport, ?LINE_ID(bus, 1), [StartStop, 5, S1, 7, TargetStop]),
  172:   gen_server_mock:expect_ets_lookup(time, time, 1234),
  173:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(StartStop, {?VEHICLE_CHECK_OUT, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
  174:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P3), ok).
  175: 
  176: next_stop_reached_case(Config) ->
  177:   StartStop = ?config(startstop, Config),
  178:   TargetStop = ?config(targetstop, Config),
  179:   Time = ?config(time, Config),
  180:   PT = ?config(pt, Config),
  181:   S1 = ?config(s1, Config),
  182:   P1 = ?config(p1, Config),
  183:   P2 = ?config(p2, Config),
  184:   P3 = ?config(p3, Config),
  185:   P4 = ?config(p4, Config),
  186:   Vehicle = ?config(vehicle, Config),
  187: 
  188:   vehicle:?CHECKIN_OK(Vehicle, StartStop, 3, true),
  189:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P1), ok),
  190:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P2), ok),
  191: 
  192:   gen_server_mock:expect_ets_lookup(public_transport, ?LINE_ID(bus, 1), [StartStop, 5, S1, 7, TargetStop]),
  193:   gen_server_mock:expect_ets_lookup(time, time, 1234),
  194:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(StartStop, {?VEHICLE_CHECK_OUT, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
  195:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P3), ok),
  196: 
  197:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(P1, {vehicle_checked_in, Vehicle}, leave),
  198:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(P2, {vehicle_checked_in, Vehicle}, stay),
  199:   gen_server_mock:expect_call(P3, {vehicle_checked_in, Vehicle}, stay),
  200:   gen_server_mock:expect_cast(S1, {?VEHICLE_CHECK_IN, Vehicle, false, gen_server_utils:extract_pid(Vehicle)}),
  201:   vehicle:?NEW_TIME(Vehicle, 1234+5, true).
  202:

  264:   P4 = ?config(p4, Config),

  267:   vehicle:?CHECKIN_OK(Vehicle, StartStop, 2, true),
  268:   ?assertEqual(vehicle:?PASSENGER_BOARD(Vehicle, P1), ok),
